comments.diff_hunk:
@@ -308,7 +308,7 @@ void BitcoinApplication::startThread()

     /*  communication to and from thread */
     connect(&m_executor.value(), &InitExecutor::initializeResult, this, &BitcoinApplication::initializeResult);
-    connect(&m_executor.value(), &InitExecutor::shutdownResult, this, &QCoreApplication::quit);
+    connect(&m_executor.value(), &InitExecutor::shutdownResult, [] { QCoreApplication::exit(0); });

comments.body:
The signal `shutdownResult` is emitted from executor's thread and this results in calling `exit()` in that thread because the connection lacks a context. But `exit()` must be called in the main thread: https://doc-snapshots.qt.io/qt6-dev/qcoreapplication.html#exit. Maybe:
```cpp
connect(&m_executor.value(), &InitExecutor::shutdownResult, this, [] {
    QCoreApplication::exit(0);
});

